                <h1>Discover the Rich History of Irish Dance</h1>
                <p>Irish dance has deep roots in ancient Celtic traditions, evolving over centuries. It gained popularity in the 19th century with the rise of social dancing. Iconic performances like Riverdance brought it to global audiences, showcasing unique footwork and rhythms. Today, Irish dance remains a symbol of culture and heritage, celebrated worldwide.</p>
